I've finally picked up my BCS and am moving on to this lizard.  Since my guild is relatively small, and we have never done VS before I have some questions on how to make this encounter work.<br>
<br>
I understand the purpose of Chain Runing, however I'm a bit baffled on how to make this work well when your enchanters are of different levels.  Right now I have a 54th, 52nd, and 46th Enchanter (Little week in the enchanter department in my guild =/ ) that I can count on being there.  I'm assuming that you want the 54th and 52nd Enchanter alternating RUNE V.  However The 52nd's rune isn't going to overwrite the 54th level rune, and the RUNE IV isn't going to overwrite either of them.  Anyone have any suggestions on how to handle this?  How do you keep the enchanters from getting creamed?  In most of our other encounters, chain runing enchanters died on the first of second cast of rune...  I'm assuming that someone like Ixilblat is a much more melee heavy fight though, so /shrug maybe they won't catch agro...<br>
<br>
Combat methods.  I've heard to different approaches.  First approach is main tank (who must be 56+) opens up defensive, taunts build agro and ~10 seconds later everyone else engages.  Everyone else is RUNE Ved already, and when they engage everyone goes full offensive.  Anyone who pulls agro off the main tank backs out of the fight until it reagros the main tank.   Second approach I've heard of, the main tank goes in with an offensive discipline.  Everything else goes pretty much the same except the melees are allowed to use disciplines.  Any recommendations on which technique to use?  Is there another?<br>
<br>
Combat force.  Our guild would probably have 3 - 4 groups there with most everyone being 50-55 maybe one group of 56+.  Does this sound like a reasonable assault force?<br>
<br>
I'll take ANY advice or recommendations you have!  Lay it on me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And if you are on the Ayonae Ro, shoot me a tell some time.<br>
