<br>
1.  The purpose of the rune is just to make sure <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> any</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> kind of rune is on the MT(s) at all times.  When VS hits he procs a nasty lifetap, but the rune negates this.<br>
<br>
2.  Warriors are the key melee to this battle, because of the lifetap.  The most common strategy I've seen is to have the tanks pop their riposte disc and go to town on him.  Riposte = no damage = no lifetap.  Some guilds I know don't allow melee types like pallys because &quot;they're free hps for VS&quot;.  I wouldn't go that far, but you definately need warriors for him.<br>
<br>
If you have the right balance, VS drops like a rock (less than 1 min).  If you don't, nasty CR.<br>
